            "<p>The principles of justice are chosen by a group of school children whose capabilities are yet to develop.</p>",
            "<p>The principles of justice are chosen by businessman, who are marooned on an uninhabited island after a shipwreck and have no possibility of returning.</p>",
            "<p>The principles of justice are chosen assuming that such principles will govern the lives of the rule makers only in their next birth if the rule makers agree that they will be born again.</p>",
            "<p>The principles of justice are chosen by potential immigrants who are unaware of the resources necessary to succeed in a foreign country.</p>"
