            "<p>The first is a finding on which the researchers base their conclusion. The second is a suggestion that might cast doubt on that finding.</p>",
            "<p>The first is an observation that supports the critic’s conclusion. The second is the critic’s conclusion.</p>",
            "<p>The first is the part of the evidence that the critic disputes. The second is a suggestion that the researchers do not accept.</p>"
