          "id": 350,
          "question": "<p><a name=\"5659\"></a><div itemprop=\"text\"><p>French cuisine is highly regarded all over the world. Yet in Paris there are more American restaurants selling burgers and fries (which many people now class as junk food) than there are in any other European capital city. &nbsp;Obviously the French are very fond of junk food, are not too proud to eat it.</p>\n\n<p>Which of the following, if true, would most weaken the author’s contention?</p>\n\n</div><br><br><b>English Language: CAT 2016 | Question: 9</b></p>",
          "type": "numeric",
