          "id": 570,
          "question": "<p><a name=\"8153\"></a><div itemprop=\"text\"><p>The passage given below is followed by four alternate summaries. Choose the option that best captures&nbsp;the essence of the passage.</p>\n\n<p>Aesthetic political representation urges us to realize that ‘the representative has autonomy with regard to the people represented’ but autonomy then is not an excuse to abandon one’s responsibility. Aesthetic autonomy requires cultivation of ‘disinterestedness’ on the part of actions which is not indifference. To have disinterestedness, that is, to have comportment towards the beautiful that is devoid of all ulterior reference to use –&nbsp;requires a kind of aesthetic commitment; it is the liberation of ourselves for the release of what has proper worth only in itself.</p>\n\n</div><br><br><b>English Language: CAT 2020 Set</b></p>",
